1
00:00:57,720 --> 00:00:58,041
Chief Editor,

2
00:00:58,641 --> 00:00:59,440
the media are all here.

3
00:01:00,001 --> 00:01:00,440
Hurry up.

4
00:01:01,321 --> 00:01:01,641
Okay.

5
00:01:06,681 --> 00:01:08,640
I know many people think online literature is not up to standard,

6
00:01:09,441 --> 00:01:10,681
and that only classic literature

7
00:01:11,081 --> 00:01:12,321
has profound philosophical thoughts.

8
00:01:13,480 --> 00:01:14,280
But I don't think so.

9
00:01:15,321 --> 00:01:16,400
I think online literature

10
00:01:16,801 --> 00:01:19,000
has always been at the forefront of social emotions.

11
00:01:20,441 --> 00:01:21,081
Sweet stories,

12
00:01:21,081 --> 00:01:21,840
thrilling stories,

13
00:01:21,840 --> 00:01:22,640
and farming stories

14
00:01:22,640 --> 00:01:23,920
The popularity of cultivation novels

15
00:01:24,560 --> 00:01:25,961
matches the complex emotions

16
00:01:25,961 --> 00:01:27,321
of the public.

17
00:01:27,920 --> 00:01:30,120
To provide a better environment for authors,

18
00:01:30,840 --> 00:01:32,441
we've reached an acquisition agreement

19
00:01:32,760 --> 00:01:34,200
with the website of Far and Wide.

20
00:01:34,321 --> 00:01:36,760
You said you'd provide a good environment,

21
00:01:36,920 --> 00:01:38,681
but why are you canceling so many contracts?

22
00:01:38,961 --> 00:01:40,480
I believe authors

23
00:01:40,721 --> 00:01:41,881
sell dreams.

24
00:01:42,560 --> 00:01:43,480
Our publishing house

25
00:01:43,801 --> 00:01:45,480
has always been a dreamland.

26
00:01:46,161 --> 00:01:48,241
I don't want it to become a junkyard.

27
00:01:48,801 --> 00:01:50,400
What's your view on the relationship

28
00:01:50,400 --> 00:01:51,681
between the author,

29
00:01:51,681 --> 00:01:52,881
the work, and the characters?

30
00:01:52,881 --> 00:01:54,601
I believe that the process of an author

31
00:01:54,801 --> 00:01:55,881
creating a work and characters

32
00:01:56,280 --> 00:01:58,120
is a continuous process of peering into their own heart

33
00:01:58,321 --> 00:01:59,640
and expressing themselves.

34
00:02:01,881 --> 00:02:03,280
And the characters in the author's work

35
00:02:04,000 --> 00:02:05,721
always bear the author's imprint

36
00:02:06,161 --> 00:02:07,360
and flow with his blood.

37
00:02:08,240 --> 00:02:09,240
But at the same time,

38
00:02:09,360 --> 00:02:11,480
they are also truly independent individuals.

39
00:02:11,881 --> 00:02:13,601
has its own will

40
00:02:14,121 --> 00:02:15,920
and follows its own fate

41
00:02:16,041 --> 00:02:17,001
towards the end.

42
00:02:19,080 --> 00:02:19,881
This is

43
00:02:20,240 --> 00:02:22,480
the world where the person who writes my fate lives.

44
00:02:24,121 --> 00:02:25,360
Where is that person now?

45
00:02:27,200 --> 00:02:29,281
Can I go back to the previous world?

46
00:02:30,721 --> 00:02:31,721
Hello, Yan Ying.

47
00:02:31,841 --> 00:02:35,080
The rules of this world have been loaded for you.

48
00:02:35,240 --> 00:02:38,800
You now have the basic knowledge and life skills of this world.

49
00:02:39,561 --> 00:02:42,640
This world and the world in the book are parallel universes.

50
00:02:43,121 --> 00:02:45,041
The entrance connecting the two worlds

51
00:02:45,041 --> 00:02:46,881
is the Qixi star chart.

52
00:02:47,281 --> 00:02:49,121
[and brought you to this world.]

53
00:02:49,200 --> 00:02:52,321
[You have only one chance to change your fate.]

54
00:02:53,041 --> 00:02:54,721
[Good luck.]

55
00:03:00,480 --> 00:03:01,281
Where's the Star Token?

56
00:03:11,441 --> 00:03:13,520
I must rewrite my ending.

57
00:03:15,240 --> 00:03:15,520
Yeah.

58
00:03:15,960 --> 00:03:17,321
Cancel all my appointments.

59
00:03:18,480 --> 00:03:20,281
I have more important things to do.

60
00:03:21,161 --> 00:03:21,401
Okay.

61
00:03:28,441 --> 00:03:29,041
Hand over the Star Token,

62
00:03:29,121 --> 00:03:29,881
and I'll spare your life.

63
00:03:30,480 --> 00:03:32,760
This is a society governed by law.

64
00:03:32,760 --> 00:03:33,800
You can't hurt people at will.

65
00:03:34,401 --> 00:03:35,281
Don't play any tricks.

66
00:03:35,401 --> 00:03:35,760
Tell me,

67
00:03:36,080 --> 00:03:36,960
where is the Star Token?

68
00:03:40,920 --> 00:03:42,520
Let me go first.

69
00:03:44,601 --> 00:03:46,480
I don't know what you're talking about.

70
00:03:46,721 --> 00:03:48,001
But if you're going to be like this,

71
00:03:48,121 --> 00:03:48,960
I can't cooperate with you.

72
00:03:52,441 --> 00:03:53,601
One more chance.

73
00:03:53,881 --> 00:03:54,360
Tell me.

74
00:03:54,680 --> 00:03:55,680
Where is the Star Symbol?

75
00:03:56,121 --> 00:03:58,121
I don't know what you're talking about.

76
00:03:58,561 --> 00:03:59,881
Let me go first.

77
00:03:59,881 --> 00:04:01,360
If your stuff is with me,

78
00:04:01,360 --> 00:04:02,401
I can help you look for it.

79
00:04:12,281 --> 00:04:12,920
Wow.

80
00:04:42,761 --> 00:04:44,041
That was really fast.

81
00:04:45,320 --> 00:04:47,120
The bike just passed us.

82
00:04:53,680 --> 00:04:54,320
You, you, you...

83
00:04:54,320 --> 00:04:55,401
Hold it back.

84
00:04:55,601 --> 00:04:56,440
Don't spit on the car.

85
00:05:35,240 --> 00:05:36,041
Where is the Star Symbol?

86
00:05:40,521 --> 00:05:41,320
Have some water.

87
00:05:42,161 --> 00:05:43,081
It'll be easier on the stomach.

88
00:05:46,961 --> 00:05:47,440
I can sit.

89
00:05:47,880 --> 00:05:48,841
I'll go change my clothes first.

90
00:05:56,601 --> 00:05:57,240
No.

91
00:05:57,880 --> 00:05:59,120
He's been dodging the whole time.

92
00:06:00,480 --> 00:06:01,521
In war,

93
00:06:01,920 --> 00:06:03,000
deception is key.

94
00:06:04,120 --> 00:06:05,920
If he hides the Star Mark somewhere else,

95
00:06:06,161 --> 00:06:06,920
and says he doesn't have it,

96
00:06:07,560 --> 00:06:08,841
I can't do anything about it.

97
00:06:16,961 --> 00:06:17,480
What are you doing?

98
00:06:17,641 --> 00:06:18,560
I'm afraid you'll run away.

99
00:06:18,560 --> 00:06:20,041
This is my home.

100
00:06:20,161 --> 00:06:21,281
You think I'll run?

101
00:06:22,521 --> 00:06:23,161
Let's talk.

102
00:06:23,480 --> 00:06:24,560
Wait till I change.

103
00:06:24,680 --> 00:06:24,961
Out.

104
00:06:25,480 --> 00:06:27,281
You're hiding the star talisman

105
00:06:27,521 --> 00:06:28,961
because you're guilty.

106
00:06:29,201 --> 00:06:29,841
I found it.

107
00:06:30,041 --> 00:06:30,641
So,

108
00:06:31,081 --> 00:06:32,081
you're kicking me out.

109
00:06:32,880 --> 00:06:34,601
You're a girl.

110
00:06:35,440 --> 00:06:36,560
Under my command,

111
00:06:36,721 --> 00:06:37,761
who dares treat me as a girl?

112
00:06:41,601 --> 00:06:42,000
Speak.

113
00:06:42,560 --> 00:06:43,360
Where is the Star Symbol?

114
00:06:46,201 --> 00:06:46,920
You won't tell me, right?

115
00:07:00,880 --> 00:07:01,841
I'll say it again.

116
00:07:02,081 --> 00:07:03,721
I don't have it.

117
00:07:04,880 --> 00:07:05,560
I don't believe you.

118
00:07:22,000 --> 00:07:22,641
Have you finished searching?

119
00:07:23,920 --> 00:07:24,401
Yes.

120
00:07:35,201 --> 00:07:36,000
Get out.

121
00:07:52,440 --> 00:07:54,240
Tell me about your background and purpose first.

122
00:07:55,800 --> 00:07:57,120
You don't need to know that.

123
00:07:57,641 --> 00:07:59,120
You just need to tell me

124
00:07:59,120 --> 00:08:00,721
where you hid the Star Symbol.

125
00:08:01,560 --> 00:08:02,560
It seems that

126
00:08:02,721 --> 00:08:04,081
there's no need to continue the negotiation.

127
00:08:06,000 --> 00:08:06,961
You want to go back on your word?

128
00:08:09,880 --> 00:08:11,601
In any form of negotiation,

129
00:08:11,920 --> 00:08:14,081
sincerity is the premise.

130
00:08:14,961 --> 00:08:16,000
If you want me to help you,

131
00:08:16,601 --> 00:08:18,281
you must tell me the truth.

132
00:08:25,721 --> 00:08:28,120
I'm General Yan Ying of Qingyun State.

133
00:08:28,360 --> 00:08:30,920
I came from a book called Galaxy Chronicle.

134
00:08:32,521 --> 00:08:33,761
This is our national treasure,

135
00:08:34,161 --> 00:08:35,320
the Qixi Star Chart.

136
00:08:36,001 --> 00:08:37,761
There used to be a star mark on it.

137
00:08:38,320 --> 00:08:39,560
But after I met you,

138
00:08:39,920 --> 00:08:40,960
it disappears.

139
00:08:43,001 --> 00:08:43,481
So?

140
00:08:43,881 --> 00:08:44,960
It's on you.

141
00:08:45,521 --> 00:08:47,200
Regardless of your origins,

142
00:08:47,481 --> 00:08:48,281
you say

143
00:08:48,641 --> 00:08:50,161
the Star Seal is a mark.

144
00:08:50,481 --> 00:08:52,200
How could it be on me?

145
00:08:52,200 --> 00:08:53,080
I saw it.

146
00:08:53,200 --> 00:08:53,680
When?

147
00:08:54,041 --> 00:08:54,881
When you kissed me.

148
00:09:12,281 --> 00:09:13,200
Who dares to disturb me?

149
00:09:14,041 --> 00:09:15,521
A vacuum robot.
